<% content_for(:title, t("settings.index.title")) %>
<h1><%= t("settings.index.heading") %></h1>

<%# Phase 29 (settings refactor) — 3-row layout.
    Phase 32 follow-up (2026-05-16) — Row 2 simplification.

    Row 1 — profile (left) + security launchers (right).
    Row 2 — Discord webhook (left) + Slack webhook (right). The
            OAuth-applications + tokens management UI moved to rake
            tasks (`bin/rails pito:oauth_apps:*` /
            `bin/rails pito:tokens:*`) — pito is single-user, the
            operator manages those from the shell. The Doorkeeper
            handshake endpoints (`/oauth/authorize`, `/oauth/token`,
            `/oauth/revoke`, `/oauth/introspect`) stay live for the
            Claude Desktop OAuth client.
    Row 3 — stack pane spanning both columns (`.pane--wide`):
            db (Postgres + Redis), search (Meilisearch + Voyage),
            storage (assets + notes).

    The dropped UI/UX, Workspace, and Voyage panes (theme,
    keyboard-navigation toggle, max_panes, pane_title_length,
    voyage_index_project_notes) all moved out of this surface in
    the refactor:

      * `max_panes` / `pane_title_length` / `timezone` →
        `config/pito.yml` (operator-level, restart Puma to apply).
      * theme → localStorage only (no server persistence).
      * keyboard navigation → always on (toggle dropped).
      * `voyage_index_project_notes` → folded into credentials
        presence (`Rails.application.credentials.voyage.api_key`).

    Security links open a layout-positioned `<dialog>` populated via
    Turbo Frame (see `_settings_modal.html.erb` +
    `settings_modal_controller.js`); the standalone routes still
    render the full pages on direct hits. %>
<%# 2026-05-16 structural fix — the `settings-modal` Stimulus
    controller used to mount on the `<dialog>` itself inside
    `_settings_modal.html.erb`. That worked for the auto-open path
    (TOTP mandatory gate — controller's `connect()` runs when the
    element enters the DOM) but broke the trigger-link path: the
    `[ sessions ]` / `[ locations ]` links in `_security_pane.html.erb`
    are siblings of the dialog, not descendants, so their click
    events never bubble through the dialog and Stimulus never fires
    `click->settings-modal#open`. The links fell through to default
    `<a>` navigation and the page full-loaded instead of opening the
    modal.

    Fix: mount the controller on a wrapper that encloses BOTH the
    panes (where the trigger links live) AND the `_settings_modal`
    partial (where the dialog lives). The dialog now carries only
    its target marker + actions; the wrapper owns the controller
    scope, so click actions on any descendant — pane links or
    in-dialog `[close]` — reach the controller correctly. %>
<div data-controller="settings-modal">
  <div class="settings-panes">
    <%# Phase F3 (Beta 4, 2026-05-20) — profile pane CUT per ADR 0016.
        Username + password management moved to operator-only rake
        tasks (`bin/rails pito:user:rename`, `bin/rails pito:user:
        password_set`). Row 1 now renders the Security pane alone. %>
    <div class="pane-row">
      <%= render "security_pane" %>
    </div>

    <%# Beta 4 — F3-B. Unified notifications panel. Collapses the
        prior two-pane Discord + Slack row into a single full-width
        panel rendering a shared toggles block at the top followed by
        the per-brand subsections (Discord, then Slack). %>
    <div class="pane-row">
      <%= render "notifications_pane" %>
    </div>

    <div class="pane-row">
      <%= render "stack_pane" %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <%# Layout-positioned settings security modal. Single dialog shared by
      all three security launchers; the Stimulus controller (mounted on
      the wrapper above) swaps the target URL into the inner Turbo
      Frame on open. %>
  <%= render "settings_modal" %>
</div>
